cEYZOSoU5RI.title: LEADING MY FIRST TOUR! The Inca Trail in Peru
cEYZOSoU5RI.description:
Leading my first ever BMTM Adventures tour in Peru!
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

After leaving behind the beaches of Southeast Asia it was time to venture into a new country: Peru. This time, it would be a whole new adventure too when I met 15 readers of the blog to take them on an epic adventure around Peru with my tour co-leader, Pete. 

In this episode we start off in Cusco, Peru, visiting the Moray, Salinas de Maras, via ferrata and ziplining in the Sacred Valley, and then the 4 day, 3 night trek down the Inca Trail to Machu Picchu. 

A few of us also hiked up Huayna Picchu, finishing with an incredible view over Machu Picchu. It was an adventure I'll never forget full of llamas, Alpacas, ancient Incan ruins, and of course, one of the seven ancient Wonders of the World. We finished our trip with none other than Rainbow Mountain. 

This was an adventure I'll never forget with people I am so privileged to have been able to bond with and bring on a tour of Peru. I long suspected it but now I know for certain: Be My Travel Muse readers are awesome! 

For more about upcoming tours and to reserve your spot on next year's Peru tour, check out the tours page on my blog: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/tours/

Special Thanks to Jennifer Garnett for lending me some of her GoPro footage, and thanks to everyone who came on the tour for being part of this video!

1X39TPsyI84.title: Nusa Penida: BALI'S BEST KEPT SECRET?
1X39TPsyI84.description:
Is Nusa Penida: BALI'S BEST KEPT SECRET?
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Bali can be pretty busy, with bad traffic, so I wanted to check out the quieter side: The Nusa Islands. 

After a few days in Nusa Lembongan and Nusa Ceningan, I wondered if there would be even more adventures in Nusa Penida, AND THERE WERE. 

This was by far my favorite part of Bali, and it really felt like Bali might have 30 years ago, like I'd heard. The roads were crazy, the cliffs were high and there were stairs to get just about everywhere, but it made the adventure amazing and gave me lots of exercise too. 

In this episode I visit the famous spots like Kelingking beach, Suwehan beach, Goa Giri Putri Cave Temple, Peguyangan Waterfall, as well as spend the night in the Rumah Pohon treehouse. 

For more on where to find each of these amazing places, plus links to each of the Airbnbs I stayed in, check out the blog posts below! 

NUSA PENIDA TRAVEL GUIDE: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/nusa-penida/
NUSA ISLANDS TRAVEL GUIDE: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/nusa-islands-itinerary/
THE TREEHOUSE!
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/rumah-pohon-nusa-penida/

vuQqCtkpOTc.title: Should Women Travel Alone in the Philippines?
vuQqCtkpOTc.description:
IS IT OKAY TO TRAVEL ALONE AS A WOMAN IN THE PHILLIPINES?
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

In my previous video about the Philippines, I talked about how initially I didn't connect with it, then had a change of heart. I was surprised to find that a lot of the comments suggested that traveling there alone is the problem, and that it's never okay to travel anywhere alone.

I've been traveling the world for over 5 years now, almost entirely solo, and I want women to know that they CAN travel alone, in the Philippines and elsewhere in the world. 

Featured in the video: Ferna Mae from Everywhere with Ferna, a solo female travel blogger from the Philippines who has been traveling solo there for over 20 years: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9u7EkSMSetk_Nx-lhdtjqA

In this video we address safety, what to expect, why solo traveling is important and amazing, and dispel myths. 

SOLO FEMALE TRAVEL BOOK: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/solo-female-travel-guidebooks/
PHILIPPINES TRAVEL GUIDE: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/philippines-guide

2vqBTu2tctg.title: This Is My Travel Tattoo Story.
2vqBTu2tctg.description:
The Stories Behind My Travel Tattoos!
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

My tattoos all have a unique story. Two are sak yants, tattoos performed by a monk in Thailand who chooses the tattoo, applies it with bamboo and an ink made of snake venom and charcoal, among other things, and then blesses it. 

Om, the tattoo on my ankle, was a testament to hiking in the Chinese and Nepalese Himalayas for the preceding three months. It's a sacred symbol at the opening of many Hindu and Buddhist Mantras and for me, an important reminder to be present. 

My biggest tattoo is a combination of the work of two amazing artists: Chaim Machlev of Dots to Lines and Jason Corbett. This tattoo encompasses sacred geometry and mandalas, a representation of the universe. These tattoos were completed in Berlin and Edinburgh. 

All of my tattoos are sacred in some way and they show my growth spiritually and as a traveler. They all have their own stories and meanings, and they are in a way, a map of where I've been. 

10 FEMALE TRAVEL BLOGGERS AND THEIR TATTOO STORIES: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/travel-tattoos-around-world/
Learn more about my journey in the last 5 years: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/kristin-addis-bio/

A big shoutout to Mike Corey for some of the Sak Yant tattoo footage in this video. Check out his channel here: https://www.youtube.com/user/friskyb

The adventure continues in Siargao in Cloud 9 surfing area with a few tears, puppies, kittens, rain, and flat tires. 

This is the behind the scenes I don't often show about when solo traveling can be tough or when things go wrong. But the silver lining is that they always seem to turn around again. This is the reality in this Siargao vlog! 

First there seem to be nothing but motorbike troubles, but then I meet a lovely family who wants to take pictures together, a kind local girl who lends a helping hand, and things just start falling into place again. It's not always sunshine and rainbows, but I am thankful for the experience, and I wanted to share it with you!

https://www.bemytravelmuse.com

I went chasing waterfalls in Lombok, and was pleasantly surprised by how stunning they all were. The Benang Stokel, which was a set of twin waterfalls (!), the popular Benang Kelambu, the Insta-worty Tiu Kelep Waterfall, and Sendang Gile, which was slightly off the beaten path, all blew me away. 

I can't believe I missed out on all of them the last time I was here, but I am glad to have came back and do their beauty justice with my own eyes. 

These waterfalls are worth checking out the next time you are in the area! Tips on when to go, how to get there, and other cool things to do in the area are all on my blog ↓↓↓

ys60dPT_N0A.title: Diving RAJA AMPAT: Underwater Paradise
ys60dPT_N0A.description:
Diving Raja Ampat in West Papua, Indonesia
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse
↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Welcome to Raja Ampat in West Papua, Indonesia. Never heard of it? This remote area in the far east of Indonesia is one of the hottest new places for diving in Indonesia. It's a large area with thousands of islets, most of which are uninhabited. It's like a Robinson Crusoe life in the middle of nowhere - the most beautiful middle of nowhere. 

I joined the Mutiara Laut liveaboard for 11 days of SCUBA diving in Raja Ampat's Misool, Penemu, and Kri areas, known for big schools of fish, Manta rays, Wobbegong sharks, reef sharks, and absolutely gorgeous islands. 

This video features underwater footage of sea turtles, tons of fish, sea fans, a wide variety of corals, and drone footage of the islands of Raja Ampat. 

The video begins in Sorong, which is the starting point for divers boarding a liveaboard in Raja Ampat. From there we head to Misool and onwards up north to Penemu. Most of the islands and beaches featured here have no other people -just birds! 

Check out these white sand beaches, incredible sunsets, and the amazing crew and ship, the Mutiara Laut. For an amazing diving experience in Raja Ampat, look no further. 

READ MORE: hhttps://www.bemytravelmuse.com/raja-ampat/

IWnYJvzjBdo.title: Secret Thailand: 8 STUNNING Hidden Places
IWnYJvzjBdo.description:
8 places in Thailand that you've never heard of before!
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse
↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Thailand's dreamy north has national parks galore and tons of amazing temples and hidden gems and down south, it's still possible to find amazing islands without a ton of other tourists. 

We went on a road trip up north and island hopping down south to find some of the best unknown parts of Thailand. We found Wat Chaloem, Pha Chor, waterfalls, two mountains in Doi Inthanon National Park and Doi Chiang Dao, as well as Koh Yao Yoi and Koh Yao Yai, the no-farang islands. 

Just when you thought you'd seen it all in Thailand, I bet there's at least one thing on this list that you've never seen or heard of before! 

Want more off the beaten path goodness? Check out my adventure tours here! https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/tours

READ MORE plus maps for how to get to these amazing places yourself: 
- Northern Thailand Road Trip: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/chiang-mai-day-trips
- Koh Yao Noi: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/koh-yao-noi

Koh Yao Noi and Koh Yao Yai are perfect for those who want an off the beaten path experience. Both islands are quiet, have plenty of gorgeous eco resorts, bungalows, and hotels to choose from, and both have beaches that you can get almost all to yourself.

3a6NgNn9KTE.title: Hiking Doi Luang Chiang Dao
3a6NgNn9KTE.description:
Hiking Doi Luang Chiang Dao in Thailand
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse
↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

How to hike Doi Luang Chaing Dao, Thailand's third tallest peak. 

Located just north of Chiang Mai in northern Thailand, Doi Luang Chiang Dao in Doi Chiang Dao National park has what must be the best view in all of Thailand. 

Usually this is a two day hike, but can it be done in one day? My adventure tour partner, Pete, and I attempt to do this 12km hike round trip in one day.

h4tuyUar7Aw.title: Northern Thailand's Hidden Gems
h4tuyUar7Aw.description:
Chiang Mai Road Trip Part Two: Wat Chaloem Phra Kiat and the Emerald Lake
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse
↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Thailand's dreamy north has national parks galore and tons of amazing day trips to take from Chiang Mai. Our second stop on our hidden Thailand road trip is Wat Chaloem Phra Kiat and the Emerald Lake. Both amazing sites are in a must less touristy Lampang Province.  

Wat Chaloem is a hidden gem of the north - this is the secret Thailand that most foreigners never see. The amazing floating pagodas are a magnificent feat of human strength and artistry. 

Next, we head to the Emerald Lake of Tham Pha National Park, another hidden gem of Lampang province. It's a sinkhole in the jungle filled with crystal clear blue water and tons of fish! It's considered holy, therefore there's no swimming or fishing, but just taking a look at it is incredible. 

For this trip, we're also joined by Pete, my adventure tour partner. Check out the tours here! https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/tours

READ MORE plus maps for how to get to these amazing places yourself: 
- Wat Chaloem: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/wat-chaloem-phra-kiat/
- Emerald Lake: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/emerald-lake-lampang-thailand/

ZE2lVNnf3a4.title: Chiang Mai Trip: Doi Inthanon National Park
ZE2lVNnf3a4.description:
Chiang Mai Road Trip Day One: Doi Inthanon National Park, Pha Chor, and Mae Ya Waterfall
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse
↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Thailand's dreamy north has national parks galore and tons of amazing day trips to take from Chiang Mai. Our first stop on our hidden Thailand road trip is Doi Inthanon National Park, Thailand's tallest peak. 

On the way, we stop by Pha Chor, an orange canyon located about an hour outside of the city. It's an easy, perfect little pit stop before we continue on our way to the Mae Ya Waterfall. 

Though Doi Inthanon National Park has many waterfalls, Mae Ya is easily one of the most beautiful, the largest, and the most impressive. It's also the least crowded since it takes an extra 40 minutes to drive to from the park entrance, but it's worth it!

Finally, we finish at the King and Queen Pagodas near the top of Doi Inthanon after a gorgeous drive. 

Check out the associated blog post for more information on the beautiful hidden parts of Thailand, accessible by day trip from Chiang Mai. 

READ MORE: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/

bjdXq17cv_8.title: How to Pack Carry On Only
bjdXq17cv_8.description:
How to Pack Carry On Only, Even for an Entire Year?
 ↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Is it possible to pack a carry on only for your vacations? What if your vacation lasts for an entire year? I’m here to show you how minimalist packing can make life easier for you without having to sacrifice variety or travel essentials.

Out of the past five years that I’ve been traveling the world, I have done carry-on only for about half of that time. It saves my back, saves me money, and ensures that I always have my stuff with me.

Some people thought I was crazy for going a whole year in Southeast Asia with only a carry-on backpack, but it was the best decision ever!

How did I do it? All of the information is in this video, including how to use packing cubes to your advantage, exactly what to bring, how to handle toiletries and makeup, and how to fit it all into the bag! 

For packing lists and more details about how to make minimalist packing work for you, check out the links below and check out the rest of the videos on the blog all with packing tips to help make traveling easier and simpler for you!

READ MORE details on the blog: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/carry-on-only/
THE PACKING LIST FOR EVERYWHERE IN THE WORLD: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/womens-travel-packing-list/

lQuNRg6xCYU.title: Gorilla Trekking in Uganda
lQuNRg6xCYU.description:
Gorilla Trekking in Bwindi Impenetrable National Forest in Uganda
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Trekking to see the magnificent gorillas in Uganda has to be in my top 10 travel experiences for sure. We trekked through the jungles of Bwindi Impenetrable National Forest for hours, eventually finding a family of gorillas, including babies and an enormous silver back! It felt safe and inviting, even though we were so close to them, watching as they chewed on leaves and the babies played. Having the opportunity to see these majestic creatures up close is something that I will remember for a very long time.

I was also the only guest in the resort I stayed at, as well as the only passenger on my flight out of Uganda! Africa is a crazy place sometimes! Click the blog post in the link below for directions on how you can recreate this experience. 

READ MORE details on the blog: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/how-to-go-gorilla-trekking-uganda/

How to hike to Jacob Hamblin arch and beyond in Coyote Gulch - Grand Staircase Escalante National Monument’s most famous hike. Most routes require you to have a 4x4 vehicle or to hike for several days, but by taking the sneaker route by repelling down the canyon wall, you can skip all of that and cut it down to just one day. 

This video details how to get to the trailhead, what to see on the way, how to get down to the canyon, and the beauty once you get there. 

READ MORE details on the blog: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/coyote-gulch-one-day-hike/

Most people go to Zion National Park in Utah and go straight for the Angel's Landing hike, but did you know that there's an alternative with even better views, no narrow parts, and slightly fewer people? Observation Point, though longer and higher up than Angel's Landing, provides an even better view of Zion Canyon in Zion National Park. 

Like most of the American Southwest, Zion’s warm orange rock will have you in awe and the views will take your breath away. If you're heading to Utah, you can't miss Observation Point!

READ MORE: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/zion-observation-point/

mqqkcleHiuc.title: Backpacking in Alaska
mqqkcleHiuc.description:
Backpacking in Alaska
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Eight days, three people, no trail, and only what we could carry on our backs. We shared the wilderness with Moose and bears, traversing over glaciers and mountains passes.

The adventure took place in Wrangell St. Elias National Park in the southeast corner of Alaska, right on the border with Canada. I'd never heard of this park before, but it's actually the largest in the United States - large enough to encapsulate six Yellostones. It's also home to the majority of the tallest mountain peaks in the US.

It was the experience of a lifetime. Come along on the adventure!  

READ MORE: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/hiking-in-alaska/

b4krlwJwOpY.title: Trekking in Kyrgyzstan - Part Two
b4krlwJwOpY.description:
Trekking in Kyrgyzstan, 8 days. Part two. 
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

Trekking in Kyrgyzstan is so gorgeous, plus it's not that crowded! In the second part of my 8-day trek out of Karakol, we summit the toughest pass yet and finally see the famous Ala Kul lake, which is framed by glaciers and is the color of the sky. 

We also descend into Karakol National Park, find a little bar hidden in a forest, and make some friends with the 'locals'.

This trek goes through Kyrgyzstan's Tian Shan Mountains in Central Asia and passes by the famous Ala Kul lake. In days 5-8, we finally see the lake, fly the drone over it, and finish the trek over the next couple of days. 

READ MORE: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/tian-shan-mountains-trekking/

Made possible with: Discover Kyrgyzstan http://www.discoverkyrgyzstan.org/des...
and Destination Karakol https://www.facebook.com/destinationk...

Music: La Musice, Wave Wave - Space Surfer
https://www.toneden.io/lamusice/post/...

Trekking in Kyrgyzstan is an amazingly beautiful experience. In the start of my 8-day trek out of Karakol, we pass through the Almalu Valley and summit four passes in three days! 

We see nomads on horses, pass by yurts, goats on the trail, and some beautiful snow-covered mountains.

This trek goes through Kyrgyzstan's Tian Shan Mountains and passes by the famous Ala Kul lake. In days 1-4, we make our way there passing several valleys with horses, goats, and sheep.

Slab City in California, featuring Salvation Mountain and East Jesus. 

Have you ever heard of Slab City, the last free place in America? I camped overnight in this squatter community and explored the next morning, flying my drone over Salvation Mountain and meeting a local who showed me his very interesting home. 

Next I explored East Jesus, a collection of upcycled art that was entertaining, eye-opening, and impressive.

ZIV2KKIC6Vs.title: Hiking White Pocket, Arizona
ZIV2KKIC6Vs.description:
White Pocket in Vermilion Cliffs National Monument, Arizona
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

HOW TO GET THERE: https://www.bemytravelmuse.com/white-pocket-tour/

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/bemytravelmuse
Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

How to hike to White Pocket in Vermilion Cliffs National Monument, Arizona, USA. 

If you don't get permits to the Wave, White Pocket is an amazing alternative! 

Join Mike Henrie and I as we drive down 4x4 roads through sand and over rocks to get to White Pocket, a crazy rock formation that looks like a combination between a turtle shell and molten lava - except it was carved by water! 

With almost nobody else around, White Pocket was a fantastic day trip adventure spanning several hours. Many thanks to Mike Henrie from Kanab Western Adventures for being my guide!

http://www.kanabwesternadventures.com/

Music: VOIA by Mochi Moshi (feat. Keii) (Arthur & Medic Remix)
https://soundcloud.com/argofox/voia-mochi-moshi-arthur-medic-remix

IKhwoeX3SKQ.title: Lushoto the 'Norway' of Tanzania
IKhwoeX3SKQ.description:
Have you heard of the Irente Viewpoint, the 'Norway' of Tanzania? 
↠ SUBSCRIBE for solo travel advice around the world ↠ http://www.youtube.com/bemytravelmuse

↠ CONNECT WITH ME: 
https://www.bemytravelmuse.com

Facebook : https://facebook.com/bemytravelmuse

This is the Incredible Irente Viewpoint in Lushoto, Tanzania, one of the most beautiful viewpoints in the whole of Africa. 

A farming area, Lushoto didn't have clear skies at first due to crop burning, but eventually the smoke cleared and we had an incredible view! Lushoto is the Norway of Tanzania. 

This was my second stop of a 5-week trip taking a Land Cruiser across Tanzania, Rwanda, and Uganda. Stay tuned for more episodes! 

Music: Great days by Joakim Karud https://soundcloud.com/joakimkarud/great-days

dEuktPf38dA.title: We Followed My Grandmother's Journal Around Europe
dEuktPf38dA.description:
This summer, my mother and I followed my Grandmother's journal around Europe. 

Granny was a solo traveler before solo traveling was cool. She wrote down all of her thoughts from her European adventures in her journal - the original travel blog. 

She led us through Heidelberg in Germany, Innsbruck in Austria, South Tyrol in Italy, and Zermatt in Switzerland. 

What we found was, even though she's not with us anymore, she was very much with us on our journey, watching from whatever paradise she resides in now. 

Thank you, Granny, for making the footsteps for us to follow.
